China to Boost Coal Production by 18% by 2015, Interfax Reports

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-06-15T09:00:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/china-to-boost-coal-production-by-18-by-2015-interfax-reports.html
China’s annual coal output will
increase to 3.79 billion metric tons by 2015 from 3.2 billion
tons last year, Interfax reported, citing a National Energy
Agency forecast.  Coal accounts for about 70 percent of the country’s energy
mix, Interfax said, citing statistics released by the China
Electricity Council.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
